    "title": {
      "rendered": "15 Lessons Learned from Donating Online to 32 Nonprofits"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/15-Lessons-Learned-Facebook.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-18439\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/15-Lessons-Learned-Facebook-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" alt=\"15 Lessons Learned Facebook\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/15-Lessons-Learned-Facebook.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/15-Lessons-Learned-Facebook.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/15-Lessons-Learned-Facebook.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/15-Lessons-Learned-Facebook.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/15-Lessons-Learned-Facebook.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a>To celebrate <strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/nonprofitorgs\" target=\"_blank\">@NonprofitOrgs</a></strong> reaching 800,000 followers on Twitter, Nonprofit Tech for Good donated $800 to 32 nonprofits, specifically $25 each to the<strong> <a href=\"https://www.awf.org/\">Africa Wildlife Foundation</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.alleycat.org/\">Alley Cat Allies</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.amazoncares.org/\">Amazon CARES</a>, <a href=\"http://www.ad-international.org/\">Animal Defenders International</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.care.org/\">CARE</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.conservation.org/\">Conservation International</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.doctorswithoutborders.org/\">Doctors Without Borders</a>, <a href=\"https://dolphinproject.net/\">Dolphin Project</a>, <a href=\"http://www.elephants.com/\">Elephant Sanctuary of Tennessee</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.famm.org\">Families Against Mandatory Minimums</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.globalelephants.org/\">Global Sanctuary for Elephants</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.greenpeace.org/\">Greenpeace</a>, <a href=\"http://www.hrw.org/\">Human Rights Watch</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.iapf.org/\">International Anti-Poaching Foundation</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.ifaw.org\">International Fund for Animal Welfare</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.mercycorps.org/\">Mercy Corps</a>, <a href=\"http://www.mercyships.org/\">Mercy Ships</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.nrdc.org/\">Natural Resources Defense Council</a>, <a href=\"http://oceana.org/\">Oceana</a>, <a href=\"http://www.operationsmile.org/\">Operation Smile</a>, <a href=\"http://www.pawsweb.org/\">Performing Animal Welfare Society</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.seashepherd.org/\">Sea Shepherd Conservation Society</a>, <a href=\"http://www.sentencingproject.org/\">Sentencing Project</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.sierraclub.org/\">Sierra Club</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.unicef.org/\">UNICEF</a>, <a href=\"http://www.wildanimalsanctuary.org/\">Wild Animal Sanctuary</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.wildlifealliance.org/\">Wildlife Alliance</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://wilderness.org/\">Wilderness Society</a>, <a href=\"http://www.womenforwomen.org/\">Women for Women International</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.wfp.org/\">World Food Programme</a>, </strong>and the<strong>\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.worldwildlife.org/\">World Wildlife Fund</a></strong>. The 32 nonprofits were bookmarked for a donation and selected because they were effective at grabbing my attention and sparking an inspiration to give through their tweets.</p>\n<p>The last time Nonprofit Tech for Good donated to a large volume of nonprofits &#8211; $25 to 28 nonprofits &#8211; 27% of the donations failed due bugs. The good news is that there were only three nonprofits that I was unable to donate to in this round of donations (thus 9%), but it was frustrating to see how many &#8220;Thank You&#8221; landing pages and &#8220;Thank You&#8221; emails are still underutilized and poorly designed (heavy on text, void of visuals, lacking in creativity). Preliminary results from the<strong> <a href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/2015NGOtechSurvey\" target=\"_blank\">2015 NGO Global Technology Survey</a></strong> reveal that social media is increasingly a primary source of online giving inspiration, but social media calls-to-follow were rarely integrated into the donation and &#8220;Thank you&#8221; process, and if they were, they were visually underwhelming.</p>\n<p>That said, donating online to 32 nonprofits is tedious! After making 12 donations it was\u00a0tempting to give up and donate to the remaining\u00a020 nonprofits through the <strong><a href=\"http://www.giveapp.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Give App</a></strong> (search &#8220;nonprofit name&#8221; &gt; Tap to Give&gt; Tap to Confirm &gt; Done), but unfortunately the lack of activity on their social media profiles tells me that the entrepreneurs behind the app have yet to receive the\u00a0funding they need to take the app to the next level and that&#8217;s too bad. Throughout the donating process I kept wishing there was a mobile app where I could donate to each nonprofit with just a couple of taps and in a fraction of the time I spent donating online. Yes, I could have used an online giving portal, but like most people, my smartphone is becoming central to my personal economics. A giving portfolio app is definitely an app whose time has come and interestingly enough while writing this post, a new app called <strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/GivolioApp\" target=\"_blank\">Givolio</a></strong> appeared in my Twitter feed that plans to launch this fall. Please let it be well-designed, functional, bug-free, and fun to use because donating to 32 nonprofits through 32 different donation forms (some of which were downright nonsensical) is not an enjoyable experience. <em>Not at all.\u00a0</em></p>\n<h1>1. Three\u00a0of the 32 nonprofits (9%) used their donation form to build their mobile list.</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.unicefusa.org/donatenow\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18378\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Unicef-61.png?resize=600%2C248\" alt=\"Unicef 6\" width=\"600\" height=\"248\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Unicef-61.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Unicef-61.png?resize=300%2C124&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"https://www.unicefusa.org/donate/donate-now-help-save-childrens-lives/20281\" target=\"_blank\">UNICEF</a></h3>\n<h1>2. One\u00a0of the 32 nonprofits (3%) accepted Bitcoin.</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.donate.iapf.org/#donatenow\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18380\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/IAPF-2.png?resize=600%2C207\" alt=\"IAPF 2\" width=\"600\" height=\"207\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/IAPF-2.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/IAPF-2.png?resize=300%2C104&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.donate.iapf.org/#donatenow\" target=\"_blank\">International Anti-Poaching Foundation</a></h3>\n<h1>3. Two of the 32 nonprofits (6%) included the option to donate\u00a0by e-check within their donation form.</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.care.org/donate\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18383\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Care7.png?resize=600%2C480\" alt=\"Care7\" width=\"600\" height=\"480\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Care7.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Care7.png?resize=300%2C240&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" />CARE</a></h3>\n<h1>4. Eleven of the 32 nonprofits (34%) included the option to donate\u00a0with PayPal within their donation form. Three nonprofits (9%) used PayPal exclusively.</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.ifaw.org/united-states/secure/donate/support-ifaws-work\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18391\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/IFAW-8.png?resize=600%2C552\" alt=\"IFAW 8\" width=\"600\" height=\"552\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/IFAW-8.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/IFAW-8.png?resize=300%2C276&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"https://www.ifaw.org/united-states/secure/donate/support-ifaws-work\" target=\"_blank\">International Fund for Animal Welfare</a></h3>\n<h1>5. Twenty-seven of the 32 nonprofits (84%) included the option to make a monthly gift within\u00a0their donation form.</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://secure.wilderness.org/site/Donation2?df_id=12340&amp;12340.donation=form1&amp;__utma=1.235079287.1442954409.1442954409.1444653269.2&amp;__utmb=1.1.10.1444653269&amp;__utmc=1&amp;__utmx=-&amp;__utmz=1.1444653269.2.2.utmcsr=google|utmccn=(organic)|utmcmd=organic|utmctr=(not%20provided)&amp;__utmv=-&amp;__utmk=148406583\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18418\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Wilderness-2.png?resize=600%2C399\" alt=\"Wilderness 2\" width=\"600\" height=\"399\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Wilderness-2.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Wilderness-2.png?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"https://secure.wilderness.org/site/Donation2?df_id=12340&amp;12340.donation=form1&amp;__utma=1.235079287.1442954409.1442954409.1444653269.2&amp;__utmb=1.1.10.1444653269&amp;__utmc=1&amp;__utmx=-&amp;__utmz=1.1444653269.2.2.utmcsr=google|utmccn=(organic)|utmcmd=organic|utmctr=(not%20provided)&amp;__utmv=-&amp;__utmk=148406583\" target=\"_blank\">The Wilderness Society</a></h3>\n<h1>6. Four of the 32 nonprofits (13%) included a\u00a0light box to convert one-time donors into monthly donors.</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://vault.sierraclub.org/ways-to-give/\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18395\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/SC7.png?resize=600%2C304\" alt=\"SC7\" width=\"600\" height=\"304\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/SC7.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/SC7.png?resize=300%2C152&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"https://vault.sierraclub.org/ways-to-give/\" target=\"_blank\">Sierra Club</a></h3>\n<h1>7. Six\u00a0of the 32 nonprofits (19%) included the option to make an honor/tribute gift within their donation form.</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://act.oceana.org/donate/2015/?amount_other=25&amp;donation_type=single&amp;prefill=1&amp;source=navigation\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18420\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Oceana-4.png?resize=600%2C515\" alt=\"Oceana 4\" width=\"600\" height=\"515\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Oceana-4.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Oceana-4.png?resize=300%2C258&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"https://act.oceana.org/donate/2015/?amount_other=25&amp;donation_type=single&amp;prefill=1&amp;source=navigation\" target=\"_blank\">Oceana</a></h3>\n<h1>8. Sixteen of the 32 nonprofits (50%) had a one-page donation form.</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://secure3.convio.net/alley/site/SPageServer?pagename=donatenow\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18435\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Alley-Cat-donation.png?resize=600%2C494\" alt=\"Alley Cat donation\" width=\"600\" height=\"494\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Alley-Cat-donation.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Alley-Cat-donation.png?resize=300%2C247&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"https://secure3.convio.net/alley/site/SPageServer?pagename=donatenow\" target=\"_blank\">Alley Cat Allies</a></h3>\n<h1>9. 25 of the 32 nonprofits (78%) had mobile responsive donation forms.</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.awf.org/donate\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18429\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/mobile-2.png?resize=300%2C502\" alt=\"mobile 2\" width=\"300\" height=\"502\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/mobile-2.png?w=300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/mobile-2.png?resize=179%2C300&amp;ssl=1 179w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><a href=\"https://www.awf.org/donate\" target=\"_blank\">Africa Wildlife Foundation</a></h3>\n<h1>10. Two of the 32 nonprofits (6%) included a &#8220;Thank You&#8221; video on their &#8220;Thank\u00a0You&#8221; landing page.</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://donate.doctorswithoutborders.org\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18385\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dcotors-8.png?resize=600%2C374\" alt=\"dcotors 8\" width=\"600\" height=\"374\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dcotors-8.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dcotors-8.png?resize=300%2C187&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"https://donate.doctorswithoutborders.org/onetime.cfm?\" target=\"_blank\">Doctors Without Borders:</a></h3>\n<h1>11. Ten of the 32 nonprofits (31%) included\u00a0a call-to-share the donation on social networks on their &#8220;Thank You&#8221; landing page. <em>Zero</em> featured a <em>visually compelling\u00a0</em>call-to-follow on social networks.</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://secure3.convio.net/gpeace/site/Donation2?df_id=3241&amp;3241.donation=form1&amp;autologin=true&amp;s_src=header\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18396\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Greenpeace-4.png?resize=600%2C381\" alt=\"Greenpeace 4\" width=\"600\" height=\"381\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Greenpeace-4.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Greenpeace-4.png?resize=300%2C191&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"https://secure3.convio.net/gpeace/site/Donation2?df_id=3241&amp;3241.donation=form1&amp;autologin=true&amp;s_src=header\" target=\"_blank\">Greenpeace</a></h3>\n<h1>12. Two of the 32 nonprofits (6%) included a poll on their &#8220;Thank You&#8221; landing page asking what inspired the donor to give.</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://support.worldwildlife.org/site/SPageServer?pagename=main_onetime&amp;s_src=AWE1603GD9A4\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18387\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/WWF-7.png?resize=600%2C576\" alt=\"WWF 7\" width=\"600\" height=\"576\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/WWF-7.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/WWF-7.png?resize=300%2C288&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"https://support.worldwildlife.org/site/SPageServer?pagename=main_onetime&amp;s_src=AWE1603GD9A4\" target=\"_blank\">World Wildlife Fund</a></h3>\n<h1>13. Two of the 32 nonprofits (6%) included a call-to-share the donation on social networks in their &#8220;Thank You&#8221; email.</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://give.womenforwomen.org/donate/?src=WSTND1\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18404\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/women-for-women-email-3.png?resize=600%2C348\" alt=\"women for women email 3\" width=\"600\" height=\"348\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/women-for-women-email-3.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/women-for-women-email-3.png?resize=300%2C174&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /><strong>Women for Women International</strong></a></h3>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">14. Seven of the 32 nonprofits (22%) included a\u00a0call-to-follow on social networks in their &#8220;Thank You&#8221; email.</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.mercycorps.org/donate\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18399\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/mercy-corps-email1.png?resize=600%2C372\" alt=\"mercy corps email\" width=\"600\" height=\"372\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/mercy-corps-email1.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/mercy-corps-email1.png?resize=300%2C186&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"https://www.mercycorps.org/donate\" target=\"_blank\">Mercy Corps</a></h3>\n<h1>15. 1 of the 32 nonprofits (3%) followed up with a &#8220;Thank You&#8221; robo call.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/robo-call-2.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18411\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/robo-call-2.jpg?resize=600%2C617\" alt=\"robo call 2\" width=\"600\" height=\"617\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/robo-call-2.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/robo-call-2.jpg?resize=292%2C300&amp;ssl=1 292w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<hr />\n<p>To gain a better understanding of how nonprofits, charities, and NGOs worldwide use online technology, Nonprofit Tech for Good is conducting the first-ever <strong><a href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/2015NGOtechSurvey\" target=\"_blank\">Global NGO Online Technology Survey</a></strong>. The data will be used to compile a report about regional differences in how NGOs raise money online, use website and email communications, and embrace social media. Depending upon your answers, completing the survey should take no longer than three minutes. Your participation is greatly appreciated!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/2015NGOtechSurvey\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18273\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/PIR-Report-Graphic-Newsletter.jpg?resize=600%2C200\" alt=\"PIR-Report-Graphic-Newsletter\" width=\"600\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/PIR-Report-Graphic-Newsletter.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/PIR-Report-Graphic-Newsletter.jpg?resize=300%2C100&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n",
      "protected": false
    },
    "excerpt": {
      "rendered": "<p>To celebrate @NonprofitOrgs reaching 800,000 followers on Twitter, Nonprofit Tech for Good donated $800 to 32 nonprofits, specifically $25 each to the Africa Wildlife Foundation,\u00a0Alley Cat Allies,\u00a0Amazon CARES, Animal Defenders International,\u00a0CARE,\u00a0Conservation International,\u00a0Doctors Without Borders, Dolphin Project, Elephant Sanctuary of Tennessee,\u00a0Families Against Mandatory Minimums,\u00a0Global Sanctuary for Elephants,\u00a0Greenpeace, Human Rights Watch,\u00a0International Anti-Poaching Foundation,\u00a0International Fund for Animal Welfare,\u00a0Mercy Corps, Mercy Ships,\u00a0Natural Resources Defense Council, Oceana, Operation Smile, Performing Animal Welfare Society,\u00a0Sea Shepherd Conservation Society, Sentencing Project,\u00a0Sierra Club,\u00a0UNICEF, Wild Animal Sanctuary,\u00a0Wildlife Alliance,\u00a0Wilderness Society, Women for Women International,\u00a0World Food Programme, and the\u00a0World Wildlife Fund. The 32 nonprofits were bookmarked for a donation and selected because </p>\n",
